cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY 

This paper is about robotic grasp detection using convolutional neural networks, which is a topic related to robotics (cs.RO) and computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also proposes a new method using a rotation ensemble module, which involves training the network with rotated weights, which is a technique related to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed method on a real-time robotic grasping task, which is related to systems and control (cs.SY).
